From 120d6c32273a7f33fe44aef289a566354b47fae5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Khiem Nguyen <khiem.nguyen.xt@renesas.com>
Date: Mon, 1 Mar 2021 14:20:59 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 07/15] uio: Use EOPNOTSUPP, not ENOTSUPP

To follow Linux upstream advice to use EOPNOTSUPP in new kernel patches,
rather than ENOTSUPP, this patch changes a return value in UIO driver.

Signed-off-by: Khiem Nguyen <khiem.nguyen.xt@renesas.com>
---
 drivers/uio/uio_pdrv_genirq.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/uio/uio_pdrv_genirq.c b/drivers/uio/uio_pdrv_genirq.c
index ffaebaa49d1e..1517b9ec2d69 100644
--- a/drivers/uio/uio_pdrv_genirq.c
+++ b/drivers/uio/uio_pdrv_genirq.c
@@ -239,7 +239,7 @@ static int priv_clk_set_div(struct uio_info *info, int div)
 
 	value = __clk_get_flags(priv->clk);
 	if (value & CLK_SET_RATE_PARENT)
-		return -ENOTSUPP;
+		return -EOPNOTSUPP;
 
 	parent = clk_get_parent(priv->clk);
 	value = clk_get_rate(parent) / div;
-- 
